<h2>Salaried vs Contract: Which is Better?</h2>
<p>A salaried ₹60,000/month (₹300/hr effective) vs a contractor at ₹500/hour working 160 hours/month = ₹80,000 gross. The contractor earns ₹20,000 more but has no PF, no paid leave, and self-funded healthcare. The true break-even point requires calculating the value of all salaried benefits.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq-section">
    <div class="faq-item"><h3>How many work hours in a year in India?</h3><p>Approximately 1,920-2,080 hours/year (240-260 working days × 8 hours), accounting for Sundays and public holidays typically = 240 working days × 8 hours = 1,920 hours/year.</p></div>
    <div class="faq-item"><h3>Should I use CTC or take-home for hourly rate?</h3><p>For comparing with a freelance hourly rate, use your take-home (net) salary as the base — since a freelancer must pay taxes and benefits from their own earnings.</p></div>
